tasks.success_criteria:
Arms fully extended when jumping into the water headfirst;
Arms touching the ears when entering the water;
Gliding underwater in a hydrodynamic position after the jump;

tasks.setup:
Deep water pool;
3 lanes;
The teacher is out of the water.
3 sinking objects;

description.en:
Technical and Physical Prerequisites:
·       Ability to swim;
·       Breath-holding capacity, being able to stay underwater for a period of time;
·       Visual analysis skills to estimate object depth.\r\n

Cognitive Prerequisites:
·       Ability to understand and follow the teacher’s instructions;
·       Decision-making skills to react appropriately to the danger signaled by waves and exit the pool;
·       Ability to act safely and responsibly in the water.

